      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD) is a pristine example of Japanese engineering, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powertrain maintains factory-spec compression and exhibits seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbochargers. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, benefiting from the lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral cornering dynamics. All vacuum lines have been refreshed with high-temp silicone, and the cooling system features an upgraded multi-core radiator to ensure optimal thermal management. The exterior retains its original factory clear coat with zero oxidation, while the interior showcases immaculate bolster integrity and fully functional original instrumentation. This is a collector-grade vehicle with a documented service history, ready for the most discerning purist.",
